          <title>Problems</title>
          <text>Active problems for this patient include amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (G12.21, diagnosed May 2023) as the primary diagnosis. Secondary problems related to ALS progression include dysphagia (R13.10, onset September 2023) requiring dietary modifications, dysarthria (R47.1, onset August 2023) with progressive impact on communication, dyspnea (R06.00, onset November 2023) now requiring nocturnal BiPAP support, generalized fatigue (R53.83), and major depressive disorder (F32.9) being managed with medication and counseling. The disease course has been consistent with limb-onset ALS with progression over approximately 18 months.</text>
